The query will use the tdb_exports table. The time window for analysis will be a rolling 24-month period, starting on '2024-04-01' and ending on '2026-03-31'. Filters will include `SHIPPING_DATE` between '2024-04-01' and '2026-03-31'. Additionally, it will filter for the specific buyer by applying `(UPPER(td.BUYER_COMPANY) LIKE '%LLC TDL TEXTILE CENTER%' OR JAROWINKLER_SIMILARITY(UPPER(td.BUYER_COMPANY), UPPER('LLC TDL TEXTILE CENTER')) > 80)` and ensure `UPPER(td.BUYER_COMPANY) IS NOT NULL AND TRIM(td.BUYER_COMPANY) <> ''`. The product filter will be for 'cotton' using `(UPPER(td.PRODUCT_DESCRIPTION) LIKE '%COTTON%' OR JAROWINKLER_SIMILARITY(UPPER(td.PRODUCT_DESCRIPTION), UPPER('COTTON')) > 80)`. No port filters are required. The metric to be aggregated is `SHIPMENT_VALUE`, which will be summed as `COALESCE(SUM(td.SHIPMENT_VALUE), 0)`. The data will be grouped by `UPPER(td.SELLER_COUNTRY)` to determine the total value from each selling country. The results will be ordered by the aggregated `total_value_usd` in descending order, and a `LIMIT 1` will be applied to identify the single top country. The final output will conceptually contain one row with columns for the `SELLER_COUNTRY` and its `total_value_usd`.
