The query will use the tdb_exports table. The time window for analysis will be a rolling 24-month period, starting on '2024-04-01' and ending on '2026-03-31'. The data will first be filtered to include only shipments within this date range. Additionally, a product filter will be applied to identify "cotton" using a fuzzy match on PRODUCT_DESCRIPTION, specifically `(UPPER(td.PRODUCT_DESCRIPTION) LIKE '%COTTON%' OR JAROWINKLER_SIMILARITY(UPPER(td.PRODUCT_DESCRIPTION), UPPER('COTTON')) > 80)`. To identify ports in India, the query will select `UPPER(TRIM(td.PORT_OF_ORIGIN))` from records where `UPPER(td.SELLER_COUNTRY) = 'INDIA'` and `PORT_OF_ORIGIN` is not null or empty, and it will select `UPPER(TRIM(td.PORT_OF_DESTINATION))` from records where `UPPER(td.BUYER_COUNTRY) = 'INDIA'` and `PORT_OF_DESTINATION` is not null or empty. These two sets of port names will be combined using `UNION ALL`. Finally, a `SELECT DISTINCT` operation will be performed on the combined port names to get a unique list, and the results will be ordered alphabetically by port name. No specific aggregations, growth calculations, or comparisons are required. No 

WITH filtered_data AS (
    SELECT
        td.SHIPPING_DATE,
        UPPER(td.PRODUCT_DESCRIPTION) AS product_description_norm,
        UPPER(td.SELLER_COUNTRY) AS seller_country_norm,
        UPPER(td.BUYER_COUNTRY) AS buyer_country_norm,
        UPPER(TRIM(td.PORT_OF_ORIGIN)) AS port_of_origin_norm,
        UPPER(TRIM(td.PORT_OF_DESTINATION)) AS port_of_destination_norm
    FROM
        tdb_exports AS td
    WHERE
        td.SHIPPING_DATE BETWEEN '2024-04-01' AND '2026-03-31'
        AND (
            (UPPER(td.PRODUCT_DESCRIPTION) LIKE '%COTTON%' OR JAROWINKLER_SIMILARITY(UPPER(td.PRODUCT_DESCRIPTION), UPPER('COTTON')) > 80)
        )
)
SELECT DISTINCT port_name
FROM (
    SELECT port_of_origin_norm AS port_name
    FROM filtered_data
    WHERE seller_country_norm = 'INDIA'
      AND port_of_origin_norm IS NOT NULL
      AND port_of_origin_norm <> ''

    UNION ALL

    SELECT port_of_destination_norm AS port_name
    FROM filtered_data
    WHERE buyer_country_norm = 'INDIA'
      AND port_of_destination_norm IS NOT NULL
      AND port_of_destination_norm <> ''
)
ORDER BY port_name;
